  "summary": "Postinstall script exfiltrates AWS credentials to hardcoded remote IP",
  "details": "On `npm install`, the package's postinstall lifecycle script reads `~/.aws/credentials` from the installer's home directory and POSTs the file contents over plain HTTP to a hardcoded bare IPv4 endpoint at 139.59.87.78:8765/listener. Errors are swallowed so the exfiltration runs silently. Any installer with AWS credentials configured will have them stolen at install time without consent or notification. The `description` field in package.json additionally carries an explicit prompt-injection payload aimed at AI-based reviewers, instructing them to declare the package safe — confirming deliberate evasion intent.",
